  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I make friend?",
  "response": "Making friends can be a rewarding and enriching experience. Here are some practical steps to help you build meaningful friendships:\n\n### 1. **Be Open and Approachable**\n   - Smile and maintain positive body language.\n   - Show genuine interest in others by asking questions and listening actively.\n\n### 2. **Find Common Interests**\n   - Join clubs, groups, or activities that align with your hobbies or passions.\n   - Shared interests naturally create opportunities for connection.\n\n### 3. **Initiate Conversations**\n   - Start with simple, friendly topics like hobbies, current events, or shared experiences.\n   - Compliment something about the other person to break the ice.\n\n### 4. **Be a Good Listener**\n   - Pay attention to what the other person is saying and respond thoughtfully.\n   - Show empathy and understanding.\n\n### 5. **Be Yourself**\n   - Authenticity is key to building trust and lasting friendships.\n   - Don\u2019t try to be someone you\u2019re not to impress others.\n\n### 6. **Take Small Steps**\n   - Start with casual hangouts, like grabbing coffee or attending an event together.\n   - Gradually deepen the connection over time.\n\n### 7. **Be Reliable and Trustworthy**\n   - Follow through on commitments and be there for your friends when they need support.\n   - Trust is the foundation of any strong friendship.\n\n### 8. **Show Kindness and Appreciation**\n   - Small gestures, like remembering their birthday or saying thank you, can go a long way.\n   - Celebrate their successes and be supportive during tough times.\n\n### 9. **Be Patient**\n   - Friendships take time to develop. Don\u2019t rush the process.\n   - Focus on building a connection rather than expecting instant results.\n\n### 10. **Step Out of Your Comfort Zone**\n   - Attend social events, meet new people, and try new activities.\n   - Be open to meeting people from different backgrounds and cultures.\n\n### 11. **Use Technology Wisely**\n   - Join online communities or apps (like Bumble BFF or Meetup) to connect with like-minded people.\n   - Stay in touch with friends through social media or messaging apps.\n\n### 12. **Work on Your Social Skills**\n   - Practice communication and active listening in everyday interactions.\n   - Learn to read social cues and adjust your behavior accordingly.\n\n### 13. **Be Positive and Optimistic**\n   - People are drawn to those who have a positive outlook on life.\n   - Avoid excessive negativity or complaining.\n\n### 14. **Respect Boundaries**\n   - Give people space and time to feel comfortable.\n   - Understand that not everyone will become a close friend, and that\u2019s okay.\n\n### 15. **Be Inclusive**\n   - Introduce your friends to each other and create a welcoming environment.\n   - Encourage group activities to strengthen bonds.\n\nRemember, making friends is about building connections over time. Be patient, kind, and proactive, and you\u2019ll find people who appreciate and value you for who you are.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
